			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE song Agro in Raid<a name="26311"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 9 04 5:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The agro is not &quot;HUGE&quot;, in fact it's very very little given that you're buffing 80 people at once.
<br />

<br />
The agro that your fellow bards got is from using it DURING a pull, when the only agro on the mobs (other than the one actually hit by the puller, presuming they used a bow or a spell) was the social agro that pulled them in the first place.  
<br />

<br />
The same thing happens when somebody casts a heal at the puller as they're coming in and gets raped. (Or heals somebody trying to FD and trains the group/raid)
<br />

<br />
The same thing happens when a roamer stumbles upon your group mid-fight and goes straight for the bard or the first person to toss a heal.
<br />

<br />
A general rule is not to use the AoE songs during pulls (ESPECIALLY if any type of FD pulling is going on), or any songs at all for that matter if even one member of your group is close to the &quot;front&quot; of the raid.
<br />

<br />
The same considerations apply for any mob that rampages.  For all intents and purposes, the &quot;rampage list&quot; acts just like a second non-agroed mob coming in to the camp.  Let the MT and any secondary/rampage tanks build hate before tossing ANY songs...in a raid of any size the tanks will be well-padded and the extra few seconds before you start landing buffs/debuffs isn't going to hurt anybody, whereas the loss of the raid's mana, resist, or HoS/OoS-tosser will.  (If getting an HoS or a round of resists going is particularly vital I'll often &quot;cheat&quot; this by casting during incoming and doing a quick fade as the song lands)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
