				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE song Agro in Raid<a name="26506"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 9 04 4:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm glad this thread is here, I was just going to post about it as well.  Another bard in my guild and I are trying to come to conclusions about this song and its ability to create agro.  I've never gotten agro while having AE mana or resist song on, even during a raid, and the target mob has never ping ponged to anyone else either.  I've even left the song on during pulls to test it a number of times (which I know I shouldnt have  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />), but there was still no agro.
<br />

<br />
However, my friend says that he's had the AE song actually cause agro, even through walls and such, during raids and in BoT groups, etc.  I've never had this happen, and have been well within range of mobs while having this song on without agroing (in places with short agro ranges like veksar and plane of hate).  We have both had opposite experiences, and so I'm very confused about the whole situation.
<br />

<br />
Are the AE songs just like the regular songs, in that the only agro they create is when they land on someone who already has agro, thus adding the bard and anyone else affected by it to the hate list?  Or can this song itself cause agro in certain instances or certain zones (or with Extended notes) just by hitting mobs (even through floors and walls, where no one else has instigated any agro yet)?  According to all my experiences (I've constantly used AE mana since 58, cept 62-63 of course), the answer is yes to the former and no to the latter.  But my experiences are more limited than many of you out there, so I'm wondering what else you can tell us about these unique AE beneficial songs.
<br />

<br />
Thanks all!
<br />
Elbereth 65 bard Cazic</span></td>
