			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AE song Agro in Raid<a name="26509"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 9 04 4:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Are the AE songs just like the regular songs, in that the only agro they create is when they land on someone who already has agro, thus adding the bard and anyone else affected by it to the hate list?</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Yes.  That's basically how it works.  I have heard of this happening, but really, when a bard gets agro while doing nothing but singing AOE, in my experience it has been one of 3 things:
<br />

<br />
1.  A monk in song range feigned and the mob comes to you.
<br />
2.  A puller or tank in song range dies before heals start landing and the mob comes to you.
<br />
3.  A mob gets only proximity agro on someone in song range and then comes to you before the person they agrod on can do anything.
<br />

<br />
Like I said, I can't guarantee you there isn't something else happening, but in my experience, these are the only ways you can get agro off AE songs.</span></td>
